        <definition>VLC_API picture_pool_t * picture_pool_NewFromFormat</definition>
        <argsstring>(const video_format_t *fmt, unsigned count) VLC_USED</argsstring>
        <name>picture_pool_NewFromFormat</name>
        <param>
          <type>const <ref refid="structvideo__format__t" kindref="compound">video_format_t</ref> *</type>
          <declname>fmt</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>unsigned</type>
          <declname>count</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Allocates pictures from the heap and creates a picture pool with them. This is a convenience wrapper for <ref refid="vlc__picture_8h_1ae7e7a3ec872a8e190e4473d8929c4256" kindref="member">picture_NewFromFormat()</ref> and <ref refid="vlc__picture__pool_8h_1ab651c4699387c345c195894c295f3989" kindref="member">picture_pool_New()</ref>.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>fmt</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>video format of pictures to allocate from the heap </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>count</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>number of pictures to allocate</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>a pointer to the new pool on success, NULL on error </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
