      <memberdef kind="function" id="vlc__picture__pool_8h_1a4930f29357650ad16bba5fd296f1568a" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>VLC_API void</type>
        <definition>VLC_API void picture_pool_Release</definition>
        <argsstring>(picture_pool_t *)</argsstring>
        <name>picture_pool_Release</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="vlc__picture__pool_8h_1a7db264f2fbaa4b83664bb62cbaddca95" kindref="member">picture_pool_t</ref> *</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Releases a pool created by <ref refid="vlc__picture__pool_8h_1a5cacb1f7f8b6342f7f71e7920f6e1513" kindref="member">picture_pool_NewExtended()</ref>, <ref refid="vlc__picture__pool_8h_1ab651c4699387c345c195894c295f3989" kindref="member">picture_pool_New()</ref> or <ref refid="vlc__picture__pool_8h_1add5679c70734e4387654c380a865f40d" kindref="member">picture_pool_NewFromFormat()</ref>.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>If there are no pending references to the pooled pictures, and the picture_resource_t.pf_destroy callback was not NULL, it will be invoked. Otherwise the default callback will be used.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="warning"><para>If there are pending references (a.k.a. late pictures), the pictures will remain valid until the all pending references are dropped by <ref refid="vlc__picture_8h_1ac6d35f6432c90cfbe6d0aa93759bed5a" kindref="member">picture_Release()</ref>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
