        <detaileddescription>
<para>Enumerates all pictures in a pool, both free and allocated.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>cb</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>callback to invoke once for each picture </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>data</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>opaque data parameter for the callback (first argument)</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Allocated pictures may be accessed asynchronously by other threads. Therefore, only read-only picture parameters can be read by the callback, typically <ref refid="structpicture__t_1a142c5b32188e3c5f5ba11612ddb92f01" kindref="member">picture_t.p_sys</ref>. Provided those rules are respected, the function is thread-safe. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
